Text.SourceString: In this cave of endless night, find stories hidden out of sight. Where words dance and secrets shine, all is known to <NPCName>Master Slime</>.
Text.LocalizedString: In this cave of endless night, find stories hidden out of sight. Where words dance and secrets shine, all is known to <NPCName>Master Slime</>.

Text.SourceString: Turn the page, and you shall see, tales as deep as the deepest sea. In my home of book and rhyme, lost in lore, you'll lose track of time.
Text.LocalizedString: Turn the page, and you shall see, tales as deep as the deepest sea. In my home of book and rhyme, lost in lore, you'll lose track of time.

Text.SourceString: Ask a question, big or small, in my books, I've stored them all. In this place of rhyme and reason, find answers, no matter the season.
Text.LocalizedString: Ask a question, big or small, in my books, I've stored them all. In this place of rhyme and reason, find answers, no matter the season.

Text.SourceString: Welcome, dear human, to my home, in this cavern of lore, I proudly reign.
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome, dear human, to my home, in this cavern of lore, I proudly reign.

Text.SourceString: Ask your questions, fear not time, for answers await in my world of rhyme.
Text.LocalizedString: Ask your questions, fear not time, for answers await in my world of rhyme.

Text.SourceString: Stars that shine and rocks that tell, nature's secrets I do spell.
Text.LocalizedString: Stars that shine and rocks that tell, nature's secrets I do spell.

Text.SourceString: Riddles wrapped in mysteries, in wise words, life's keys.
Text.LocalizedString: Riddles wrapped in mysteries, in wise words, life's keys.

Text.SourceString: In fields so wide where crops do grow, humans toil, seeds they sow. With sun and rain, they tend their land, reaping harvests with hardworking hands.
Text.LocalizedString: In fields so wide where crops do grow, humans toil, seeds they sow. With sun and rain, they tend their land, reaping harvests with hardworking hands.

Text.SourceString: From lands afar, to my cave you've roamed, seeking knowledge in my tome-filled home.//A seeker of truth, in pages deep, where secrets of the world do sleep.
Text.LocalizedString: From lands afar, to my cave you've roamed, seeking knowledge in my tome-filled home.//A seeker of truth, in pages deep, where secrets of the world do sleep.

Text.SourceString: In your eyes, a spark I see, a thirst for knowledge.
Text.LocalizedString: In your eyes, a spark I see, a thirst for knowledge.

Text.SourceString: In your hands, the future lies, beneath the sun, the open skies.//A journey grand, with much in store, each day a chance to learn more.
Text.LocalizedString: In your hands, the future lies, beneath the sun, the open skies.//A journey grand, with much in store, each day a chance to learn more.

Text.SourceString: Ah, farmer friend, with soil-stained hand, you hold the heart of this fertile land.//Seeds you sow, with care and might, bringing forth life from the soil's plight.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, farmer friend, with soil-stained hand, you hold the heart of this fertile land.//Seeds you sow, with care and might, bringing forth life from the soil's plight.

Text.SourceString: In your fields, green and grand, you work the wonders of the land. With each crop, with each row, you help the world around you grow.
Text.LocalizedString: In your fields, green and grand, you work the wonders of the land. With each crop, with each row, you help the world around you grow.

Text.SourceString: Farmer, in your hands lies earth's fate, with each seed you cultivate.
Text.LocalizedString: Farmer, in your hands lies earth's fate, with each seed you cultivate.

Text.SourceString: To feed the world, a noble call, in your garden, great and small.//Vegetables, fruits, grains so fine, in your care, they truly shine.
Text.LocalizedString: To feed the world, a noble call, in your garden, great and small.//Vegetables, fruits, grains so fine, in your care, they truly shine.

Text.SourceString: Rain comes down, a gentle boon, turning fields to a fertile tune. For your crops, a gift so fine, with each drop, they'll grow and shine.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain comes down, a gentle boon, turning fields to a fertile tune. For your crops, a gift so fine, with each drop, they'll grow and shine.

Text.SourceString: When the rain kisses the earth, dear farmer, it brings rebirth. In each droplet, life anew, a dance of water and morning dew.
Text.LocalizedString: When the rain kisses the earth, dear farmer, it brings rebirth. In each droplet, life anew, a dance of water and morning dew.

Text.SourceString: Storms may rage, wild and free, a farmer's challenge, as you can see. Hold steadfast as winds do blow, for after storms, crops will grow.
Text.LocalizedString: Storms may rage, wild and free, a farmer's challenge, as you can see. Hold steadfast as winds do blow, for after storms, crops will grow.

Text.SourceString: Thunder roars, lightning strikes, nature's drama, full of might. Nature’s fury, wild and vast, in its time, it too shall pass.
Text.LocalizedString: Thunder roars, lightning strikes, nature's drama, full of might. Nature’s fury, wild and vast, in its time, it too shall pass.

Text.SourceString: Snowflakes fall, a white array, covering fields where they lay. In this blanket, cold and deep, your land rests in winter's sleep.
Text.LocalizedString: Snowflakes fall, a white array, covering fields where they lay. In this blanket, cold and deep, your land rests in winter's sleep.

Text.SourceString: A winter quilt of snow so bright, under stars, it glows at night. Rest now, farmer, take your ease, as snow covers the sleeping trees.
Text.LocalizedString: A winter quilt of snow so bright, under stars, it glows at night. Rest now, farmer, take your ease, as snow covers the sleeping trees.

Text.SourceString: Cold days come, the sun hangs low, over fields, a chilly glow. Embrace this time to plan and ponder, for with spring, your fields will wander.
Text.LocalizedString: Cold days come, the sun hangs low, over fields, a chilly glow. Embrace this time to plan and ponder, for with spring, your fields will wander.

Text.SourceString: Patient farmer, wait and see, spring's return, green and free.
Text.LocalizedString: Patient farmer, wait and see, spring's return, green and free.

Text.SourceString: Summer's warmth spreads far and wide, in its embrace, we all reside.//Long days of sun, skies of blue, in summer's glow, life feels anew.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer's warmth spreads far and wide, in its embrace, we all reside.//Long days of sun, skies of blue, in summer's glow, life feels anew.

Text.SourceString: In the heat of the summer day, the world's alive in a vibrant way.//Fields of green and flowers bright, basking in the endless light.
Text.LocalizedString: In the heat of the summer day, the world's alive in a vibrant way.//Fields of green and flowers bright, basking in the endless light.

Text.SourceString: As the stars twinkle in summer night, the world rests in gentle light.//Dreams take flight in the warm air, in summer's magic, none compare.
Text.LocalizedString: As the stars twinkle in summer night, the world rests in gentle light.//Dreams take flight in the warm air, in summer's magic, none compare.

Text.SourceString: As a slime of size so grand, I glide and slide across the land.//In my form, both large and wide, many secrets I do hide.
Text.LocalizedString: As a slime of size so grand, I glide and slide across the land.//In my form, both large and wide, many secrets I do hide.

Text.SourceString: Large in size, yet gentle still, I move with a scholarly will.//Through corridors wide, I glide with ease, in my presence, minds find peace.
Text.LocalizedString: Large in size, yet gentle still, I move with a scholarly will.//Through corridors wide, I glide with ease, in my presence, minds find peace.

Text.SourceString: Books, tomes of wisdom rare, within their pages, knowledge fair.//In bindings old, secrets untold, tales of courage, truths unfold.
Text.LocalizedString: Books, tomes of wisdom rare, within their pages, knowledge fair.//In bindings old, secrets untold, tales of courage, truths unfold.

Text.SourceString: From stories old to tales anew, books offer adventures true.
Text.LocalizedString: From stories old to tales anew, books offer adventures true.

Text.SourceString: Good day, dear <PlayerName>$player</>, in quest you roam, seeking knowledge to call your own.
Text.LocalizedString: Good day, dear <PlayerName>$player</>, in quest you roam, seeking knowledge to call your own.

Text.SourceString: Greetings, traveler, in realms unknown, seeking truths yet to be shown.
Text.LocalizedString: Greetings, traveler, in realms unknown, seeking truths yet to be shown.

Text.SourceString: Welcome, friend, with curious mind, in the realm of books, may treasures you find.
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome, friend, with curious mind, in the realm of books, may treasures you find.

Text.SourceString: Books, my cherished trove, their pages hold the wisdom I strove.//Yet in the darkness of night's keep, their edges suffer from the rats' reap.
Text.LocalizedString: Books, my cherished trove, their pages hold the wisdom I strove.//Yet in the darkness of night's keep, their edges suffer from the rats' reap.

Text.SourceString: Rats, pests of the night, their nibbling bites a vexing sight.//But though they nibble, tear, and shred, my wisdom's light can't be misled.
Text.LocalizedString: Rats, pests of the night, their nibbling bites a vexing sight.//But though they nibble, tear, and shred, my wisdom's light can't be misled.

Text.SourceString: Drips and drops, a watery spree, they find their way, where books should be.//In my cavern, where wisdom rests, leaks intrude, unwelcome guests.
Text.LocalizedString: Drips and drops, a watery spree, they find their way, where books should be.//In my cavern, where wisdom rests, leaks intrude, unwelcome guests.

Text.SourceString: From ceiling high, they trickle down, staining pages, a silent frown. In pools of water, secrets drown, where once was dry, now damp is found.
Text.LocalizedString: From ceiling high, they trickle down, staining pages, a silent frown. In pools of water, secrets drown, where once was dry, now damp is found.

Text.SourceString: Laughter echoes, their voices loud, disturbing the peace, that once was proud.
Text.LocalizedString: Laughter echoes, their voices loud, disturbing the peace, that once was proud.

Text.SourceString: Outside my cave, humans make noise, dancing and shouting, without any poise.
Text.LocalizedString: Outside my cave, humans make noise, dancing and shouting, without any poise.

Text.SourceString: Nearby, in trees, the monkeys swing, their chatter loud, a constant ring.//Their playful antics, though full of glee, disturb my quiet, serenity.
Text.LocalizedString: Nearby, in trees, the monkeys swing, their chatter loud, a constant ring.//Their playful antics, though full of glee, disturb my quiet, serenity.

Text.SourceString: As darkness falls and the world grows still, I feel at peace, a quiet thrill.
Text.LocalizedString: As darkness falls and the world grows still, I feel at peace, a quiet thrill.

Text.SourceString: In the gentle night's embrace, I find solace, a peaceful space.//Human noises pierce the tranquil night, disturbing my unwind. In their clamor, I find frustration, their disruptions unkind.
Text.LocalizedString: In the gentle night's embrace, I find solace, a peaceful space.//Human noises pierce the tranquil night, disturbing my unwind. In their clamor, I find frustration, their disruptions unkind.

Text.SourceString: From constellation to celestial chart, the heavens hold knowledge, vast and smart.//In the patterns of the cosmic array, lies the wisdom of night and day.
Text.LocalizedString: From constellation to celestial chart, the heavens hold knowledge, vast and smart.//In the patterns of the cosmic array, lies the wisdom of night and day.

Text.SourceString: As stars twinkle in their distant flight, they whisper secrets in the silent night.
Text.LocalizedString: As stars twinkle in their distant flight, they whisper secrets in the silent night.

Text.SourceString: Traveling far and wide isn't a journey I choose. I prefer the comfort of my cave, where I never lose.
Text.LocalizedString: Traveling far and wide isn't a journey I choose. I prefer the comfort of my cave, where I never lose.
